{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"ir","display_name":"R","language":"R"},"language_info":{"name":"R","codemirror_mode":"r","pygments_lexer":"r","mimetype":"text/x-r-source","file_extension":".r","version":"4.0.5"}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/asadha/bellabeat-v-2?scriptVersionId=97738569\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown","outputs":[],"execution_count":0},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# About\n\nBellabeat is a small women's health tech manufacturer. \n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Asking Questions\n\n- What are some observable trends in the fitbit smart device data?\n- How do users use other samrt devices?\n- Who should we market to?\n- What are some ways we could improve the devices, such as what data is valuable for the customer?","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Business Task\n\nBased on the trends from the smart data devices, how can Bellabeat improve their devices and marketing to improve their service and sales.\n\n# Preparing and Processing the Data\n## Preparation\nFirstly, I loaded the relevant packages required for me to perform this project on R Studio:","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"library(tidyverse)\nlibrary(ggplot2)\nlibrary(tidyr)\nlibrary(readr)\nlibrary(dplyr)\nlibrary(lubridate)\nlibrary(tibble)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-27T03:56:03.293552Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-27T03:56:03.295252Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-27T03:56:03.319784Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Next, I downloaded the public dataset from Kaggle onto my nmacbook and then uploaded  the data flies I deemed relevant to R Studio program.\n## About the data\nThe data available for this project comes from a public domain(AWS) and is open access. The fitbit tracker recorded physical activity, heart rate, and sleep for thirty consenting fitbit user in April and May of 2016 for thirty days. This is a small sample size, meaning the information pulled from this analysis won't be statistically significant.\n## Sorting and Filtering the Data\nOnce the data was uploaded to R studio, i previewed the files to get a better understanding about what was in the data sets. The recognized that the minute and hourly data had been summed up in the activity file, so I did not use those datasets.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"weight <- read_csv(\"../input/fitbit/Fitabase Data 4.12.16-5.12.16/weightLogInfo_merged.csv\")\nsleep <- read_csv(\"../input/fitbit/Fitabase Data 4.12.16-5.12.16/sleepDay_merged.csv\")\nactivity <- read_csv(\"../input/fitbit/Fitabase Data 4.12.16-5.12.16/dailyActivity_merged.csv\")\nheartrate_seconds_merged <- read_csv(\"../input/fitbit/Fitabase Data 4.12.16-5.12.16/heartrate_seconds_merged.csv\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-27T03:56:03.322251Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-27T03:56:03.323606Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-27T03:56:05.17891Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"removed some unnecessary data","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"activity$SedentaryActiveDistance <- NULL\nweight$Fat <- NULL","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-27T03:56:05.182374Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-27T03:56:05.183875Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-27T03:56:05.198374Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"saw discrepency(77/940 observations), 0 shouldn't be value for total steps, may not have used the watch on these days\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"activity.v2 <- subset( activity, TotalSteps!=0 )\nsum(activity$TotalSteps == 0)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-27T03:56:05.20127Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-27T03:56:05.202723Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-27T03:56:05.21933Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Following that I took time to review the \n# Analysis\nLet's look at some stats","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"min(heartrate_seconds_merged$Value)\nmax(heartrate_seconds_merged$Value)\nsummary(activity)\nsummary(heartrate_seconds_merged)\nsummary(sleep)\nsummary(weight)\nsummary(heartrate_seconds_merged)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-27T03:56:05.221699Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-27T03:56:05.22309Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-27T03:56:06.682563Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"heart rate(want to know average~heart rate) of each user\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"avg_hr <- group_by(heartrate_seconds_merged, Id) %>% summarize(hr = mean(Value))\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-27T03:56:06.684811Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-27T03:56:06.686104Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-27T03:56:06.859596Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Findings\nvisualization(draw conclusion that we need to reach to larger audience to improve and monitor health)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"ggplot(avg_hr, aes( x = Id, y = hr)) + geom_point(shape=23, fill=\"red\", color=\"black\", size=4)\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-27T03:56:06.861886Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-27T03:56:06.863185Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-27T03:56:07.052504Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"According to fitbit(from AHA and WHO) it is recommended individuals perform 150 minutes of moderate or 75 minutes activity a week, or some combination of both(~20 total moderate minutes a day.\nThus I need to make a score chart with fairly active minutes as the base and very active as twice as much","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"activity.v3 <- mutate( activity.v2, weighted_VeryActiveMinutes = VeryActiveMinutes*2)\nactivity.v3$total_moderate_minutes <- rowSums( activity.v3[,c(\"FairlyActiveMinutes\", \"weighted_VeryActiveMinutes\")])\nactivity.v4 <- activity.v3 %>% add_column(DailyRecommendedCardio = if_else(activity.v3$total_moderate_minutes >= 20, TRUE, FALSE), .after = \"total_moderate_minutes\")\nggplot(activity.v4, aes(x= total_moderate_minutes, color= DailyRecommendedCardio)) + geom_histogram(fill= \"white\") + ggtitle(\"Distribution of Daily Activity\")\nsum(activity.v4$DailyRecommendedCardio)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-27T03:56:07.054954Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-27T03:56:07.056331Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-27T03:56:07.376813Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Out of the 863 days, users only met their daily recommended activity 492 of those days(57%). \n\n# What now?\n\nI found that many of the users fell in typically healthy heart rates between 60-100 bpm. \n\nAdditionally, there was a slight upward trend in steps by user correlating to how long they used the smart devices. The results were not significant and required further research but these smart devices could motivate users to form better habits.\n\nA great marketing strategy could be advertising to individuals battling chronic health issues. This would give them an opportunity to monitor and have control and understanding over their health. ","metadata":{}}]}